		<article class="pingback odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1  " id="comment-311" itemprop="comment" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Comment">
			<div class="comment-wrapper">
				<figure class="gravatar"></figure>
				<div class="comment-meta post-meta" role="complementary">
					<h2 class="comment-author">
													<a class="comment-author-link" href="http://blogs.sophos.com/2014/02/26/whats-coming-in-sophos-utm-accelerated-9-2-5-advanced-threat-protection-atp/" itemprop="author">What’s coming in Sophos UTM Accelerated (9.2): #5 &#8211; Advanced Threat Protection (ATP) | Sophos Blog</a>
											</h2>
					<time class="comment-meta-item" datetime="2014-02-26T09:53-05:00" itemprop="datePublished"><a href="#comment-311" itemprop="url">26 February 2014 at 9:53 am</a></time>
														</div>
				<div class="comment-content post-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>[&#8230;] date. That means the technology to protect you from viruses, email spam, web and other malware, phishing attacks, etc. Those are still the most common tools used in the initial stages of a targeted [&#8230;]</p>
					<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='https://news.sophos.com/en-us/2014/01/03/spam-emails-delivering-social-engineering-attacks-how-to-protect-your-business-users/?replytocom=311#respond' data-commentid="311" data-postid="23499" data-belowelement="comment-311" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to What’s coming in Sophos UTM Accelerated (9.2): #5 &#8211; Advanced Threat Protection (ATP) | Sophos Blog" aria-label='Reply to What’s coming in Sophos UTM Accelerated (9.2): #5 &#8211; Advanced Threat Protection (ATP) | Sophos Blog'>Reply</a>				</div>
